..TEXT:
|dismaga~: The verb ^dismagare~ (OFr ^esmaier~)
means "to reduce," "to deprive of."  In a different context it
can have the meaning of "turn aside," "distract," or "dismay,"
its English cognate (cf. ^Inf.~ XXV, 146).
