..TEXT:
|vadi~ = ^vada.~  |mia bella figlia~: Constance (see vs.
143), daughter of Manfred and Beatrice of Savoy.  In 1262 she
married Pedro III of Aragon, by whom she became the mother of
Alfonso (king of Aragon, 1285-91), James (king of Sicily, 1285-
95; king of Aragon, 1291-1327), and Frederick (king of Sicily,
1296-1337).  It was through his marriage with Constance that
Pedro III claimed the crown of Sicily, which he assumed in 1282
after the Sicilian Vespers.  Constance died at Barcelona in 1302,
having outlived both her husband and her eldest son.
..TCHR:
